commit.message:
Remove duplicate netlink macros

These are already defined by <linux/netlink.h>. I don't think we need to
redefine them here.

configure.ac: Use global instead of main fragment in __attribute__ checks

The first argument of AC_COMPILE_IFELSE is intended for top-level
constructs, not just #include directives.  Stop using } â€¦ { to
put top-level constructs into the main code fragment in the second
argument.

This fixes a build failure with future compilers.

Link to GitHub for bug reports and pull requests

I don't always have time to reply to emails so it wouldn't be fair of me to ask
people to email me and then leave them waiting.

For questions, the IRC channel (see `doc/book/src/getting-started/support.md`)
seems to work well. There's a good number of knowledgeable people in there at
almost all times.
Release version 3.1.0

Warn about missing logs if forking with NOSYSLOG set

When forking into the background, we rebind the stdout and stderr file
descriptors to `/dev/null`, discarding any logs. Print a warning about
that when `-S` (`--nosyslog`) is used without `-i` (`--foreground`) or
`-I` (`--stdio`).

contrib: remove `-S` (`--nosyslog`) from systemd unit files

`oidentd.service` is `Type=forking`, and oidentd disconnects from the
parent's stdout/stderr after forking (as it should). That means that,
with `-S`, all logs are sent to `/dev/null`.

This commit also updates `oidentd@.service`, though that is just for
consistency (since it doesn't fork).

freebsd5: replace ucred with xucred

FreeBSD 5 introduced the `xucred` struct for external users in commit
c0511d3b58c985e17c0c23585ea7d16b6f52fe61 to avoid breaking user space
applications when the `ucred` struct changes.

oidentd happened to still work after this commit because the EUID it
reads was stored at the same location in both structures. This is no
longer the case with FreeBSD 13.

This commit updates the freebsd5 module to use `xucred` instead of
`ucred` as the expected return type for getcred calls.

not compile on recent versions of FreeBSD.

Kernel module `freebsd.c` hasn't been updated in a long time and does
not compile on recent versions of DragonFly BSD.
Drop support for very old FreeBSD versions
Fail on non-zero EUID if NEED_ROOT is set
autogen: replace echo with printf

autogen: don't redirect stderr in require_binary

On OpenBSD, `automake` et al. are wrappers that write a message to
standard error if `AUTOCONF_VERSION`/`AUTOMAKE_VERSION` is not set.

Not redirecting standard error should make it more obvious why we
weren't able to find a usable `autoconf` or `automake` executable.
